<item>
            <title>[LU-16819] Using &quot;uname -r&quot; in lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4 limits building to the currently running kernel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16819</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using &quot;uname -r&quot; anywhere in the build process limits building to the currently running kernel. This is bad since it&apos;s quite common to build for multiple kernels when doing DKMS builds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This shows up in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16659&quot; title=&quot;mofed detection would detect multiple OFED installed by mistake for multiple kernels installed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16659&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16659&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
